BOLU-OLU ESHO AKURE – Men of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), Ondo State Command, have bust an international cyber syndicate defrauding Nigerians through threat to life, obtaining by false pretence, cultism and other methods. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Briefing newsmen on Tuesday in Akure, the state capital, after parading an a Nigeria-based accomplice of the syndicate, the state commandant, Christiana Abiakam-Omanu, disclosed that, “Information through our intelligence gathering revealed that a syndicate of Nigerians in Oman was suspected to have obtained the victims by false pretence. “An accomplice to the suspect based in Nigeria, Akinlosotu Emmanuel, has been arrested while others are being tailed by our men. “Currently, efforts are made to repatriate the notorious foreign based suspects, who are Oladipupo Paulina and Shipe Alaba.” She said that another syndicate that scammed middle age women through phoney love was also bust by the operatives of the formation. The commandant said: “In another development, another dangerous syndicate involving internet love scam targeting middle age women has been arrested by our specially trained officers.